ad. We continue talking and drinking our drinks until the server returns, at which time we tell her that we haven't decided on an entree but we would like more salad and breadsticks. She brings it, and we do the same thing - pour them into the bag. In a few more minutes she comes back and we order some cheap wine and more salad and breadsticks. So she brings back the wine, salad, and breadsticks. We drink the wine and put the rest in the bag. When she comes back we finally order an entree and say that we would like more salad and breadsticks. We always say please, and she seems to be OK with all the salad and breadsticks we are ordering. She comes back shortly with the salad and breadsticks. She has to; it's her job. This goes on for a while. We order salad and breadsticks several more times before our meals come, and while we are picking at our meals we order even more salad and breadsticks. We also order salad and breadsticks with our dessert and again with our coffee. The bags are getting pretty full by the end of the night.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Somehow we managed to drag out the huge bags without anyone noticing.&lt;br /&gt;Throwing handfuls of salad off the side.&lt;br /&gt;Then the cops showed up.&lt;br /&gt;We ran.&lt;br /&gt;Salad and breadsticks everywhere.&lt;br /&gt;Sliding around on salad dressing.&lt;br /&gt;More stuff happens.&lt;br /&gt;Salad and breadsticks.&lt;br /&gt;Food.</content><link rel='alternate' type='text/html' href='http://blog.allometric.net/2007/04/this-is-what-we-do-on-my-sisters.html' title='this is what we do on my sister&apos;s birthday'/><link rel='replies' type='text/html' href='http://www.blogger.com/comment.g?blogID=30719777&amp;postID=3031785219862004014' title='1 Comments'/><link rel='replies' type='application/atom+xml' href='http://blog.allometric.net/feeds/3031785219862004014/comments/default' title='Post Comments'/><link rel='self' type='application/atom+xml' href='http://www.blogger.com/feeds/30719777/posts/default/3031