5732004121554381</id><published>2007-02-08T22:13:00.000-08:00</published><updated>2007-04-04T22:18:48.148-07:00</updated><title type='text'>ellesmere island</title><content type='html'>&lt;a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://bp1.blogger.com/_GXjpWAjxWHA/RhRoxPVbIfI/AAAAAAAAABU/K24UhhVxIBs/s1600-h/cainville_cloud.jpeg"&gt;&lt;img style="margin: 0px auto 10px; display: block; text-align: center; cursor: pointer;" src="http://bp1.blogger.com/_GXjpWAjxWHA/RhRoxPVbIfI/AAAAAAAAABU/K24UhhVxIBs/s400/cainville_cloud.jpeg" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5049776277328437746" border="0" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Had all this incoming radiation&lt;br /&gt;been striking a larger area,&lt;br /&gt;it might have made all the difference.&lt;br /&gt;Glancing angles offer less intensity,&lt;br /&gt;but allow one to absorb more&lt;br /&gt;in the course of a day.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Our aspect was obviously too direct&lt;br /&gt;and we were melting by noon.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The Law of Cosines&lt;br /&gt;is not in itself meaningful,&lt;br /&gt;but as we are now&lt;br /&gt;a pair of low-latitude puddles,&lt;br /&gt;we're inclined to make meaning of it.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;So then, we agree on meaninglessness,&lt;br /&gt;but there is still a reason that spring&lt;br /&gt;in Ecuador is so different&lt;br /&gt;than spring on Ellesmere.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;*****&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;I have a class in Environmental Optics this semester.... hence the geophysics.</content><link rel='alternate' type='text/html' href='http://blog.allometric.net/2007/02/ellesmere.html' title='ellesmere island'/><link rel='replies' type='text/html' href='http://www.blogger.com/comment.g?blogID=30719777&amp;postID=155732004121554381' title='0 Comments'/><link rel='replies' type='application/atom+xml' href='http://blog.allometric.net/feeds/155732004121554381/comments/default' title='Post Comments'/><link rel='self' type='application/atom+xml' href='http://www.blogger.co