 the walls of my little room&lt;br /&gt;So I turned sideways and squeezed through the door&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;And went out to the front lawn to get some air&lt;br /&gt;The sun and breezes felt good, and I smiled even more&lt;br /&gt;The people walking down my street to the park&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Were looking a little worried about my giant grin&lt;br /&gt;Rocking back and forth out on the front lawn in the sun&lt;br /&gt;The dog got nervous, started barking, and ran off&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;I smiled bigger and the powerlines started to snap&lt;br /&gt;Mothers gathered up the children in their arms and ran&lt;br /&gt;Buildings started to topple under my huge lower lip&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The interstate clogged with cars evacuating the city&lt;br /&gt;Soon it got dark and started to rain, but I was still happy&lt;br /&gt;So my smile stretched even wider across the city&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;It was rocking back and forth across the whole valley&lt;br /&gt;Choppers were circling and shining spotlights through the rain&lt;br /&gt;And there were copcars with their lights on all around&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;A bunch of sirens were wailing and horns were honking&lt;br /&gt;All the lights were reflecting off of my big wet lips and teeth&lt;br /&gt;And people in the choppers shouted with megaphones&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;One megaphone was shouting about depressing things&lt;br /&gt;Like dead puppies, despair, cancer, politics, franchises, and war&lt;br /&gt;Another was ex-girlfriends complaining about stuff I did&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;But I kept smiling anyways&lt;br /&gt;I couldn't help it&lt;br /&gt;I was happy&lt;/div&gt;</content><link rel='alternate' type='text/html' href='http://blog.allometric.net/2006/07/my-happiest-day.html' title='My happiest day'/><link rel='replies' type='text/html' href='http://www.blogger.com/comment.g?blogID=30719777&amp;postID=115414561000153677' title='0 Comments'/><link rel='replies' type='application/atom+xml' href='http://b